        "id": 1040868
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-04T02:03:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this change is very unfortunate.  are you sure we can\u0027t structure this differently ?",
      "revId": "2f47c976aff7f54f2ee4aee22c186fc4fea077df",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "06abab62_85c377ba",
        "filename": "libminijail.h",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 353,
      "author": {
        "id": 1825476
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-04T02:32:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "One thing I tried was to introduce a `minijail_enter_internal` that takes two arguments (the const `struct minijail *j` and a pointer to a mutable struct that holds the FD), but that required a significant rewiring. Plus I couldn\u0027t find any instance of any caller in Android or CrOS where the constness mattered.\n\nI can take this change back to that state if the code size and complexity increase is tolerable.",
      "parentUuid": "f290e285_7fd0db8b",
      "revId": "2f47c976aff7f54f2ee4aee22c186fc4fea077df",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a8e20b39_06c8ef15",
        "filename": "libminijail.h",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 353,
      "author": {
        "id": 1825476
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-04T02:41:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "ah scratch that, I just remembered that it would make `minijail_enter()` to not support the notification fd at all, since there is no way of notifying back the fd to the caller. even passing it through a fd could cause the state to be invalid if somebody tried to call `minijail_enter()` multiple times with the same object (which is something that\u0027s completely legal to do right now).\n\nso there needs to be _some_ API change to make this work :/ this was the path of least resistance / change.",
      "parentUuid": "06abab62_85c377ba",
      "revId": "2f47c976aff7f54f2ee4aee22c186fc4fea077df",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3fec9945_fe841751",
        "filename": "libminijail.h",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 353,
      "author": {
        "id": 1825476
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-04T03:49:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the only other option that i can think of is to have the user pass in one half of the socketpair to the `minijail_set_seccomp_filter_install_user_notification()` function and let them do the `receive_fd()` bit. but that has the downside of forcing the caller to whitelist the `sendmsg(2)` syscall (which I wanted to avoid doing, since we do have one use case where that needs to not be allowed).",
      "parentUuid": "a8e20b39_06c8ef15",
      "revId": "2f47c976aff7f54f2ee4aee22c186fc4fea077df",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
